what semi-colons do. A lot of people don't

00:37:01.840 --> 00:37:07.830
like semi-colons anymore and I have no idea
why. But they're very useful. You use them

00:37:07.830 --> 00:37:14.270
to join two main clauses when the main clauses
are conceptually related to each other, when

00:37:14.270 --> 00:37:19.030
they have something to do with each other.
Ben coming along definitely has to do with

00:37:19.030 --> 00:37:23.570
Beth going to yoga class. They're very related
ideas. So it would be completely valid to

00:37:23.570 --> 00:37:29.109
use a semi-colon right here to fix that run-on
sentence. You can also use a comma with a

00:37:29.109 --> 00:37:35.859
conjunction. You could say, 'Beth went to
a yoga class COMMA and Ben came along.' So

00:37:35.859 --> 00:37:41.170
there are lots of ways to fix run-on sentences
